data.chText: 变体；变种；型式
data.enText: a form of sth that is slightly different from an earlier form or from other forms of the same thing

data.chText: 这游戏有两个版本，一长一短。
data.enText: There are two versions of the game, a long one and a short one.

data.chText: 软件包的最新版本
data.enText: the latest version of the software package

data.chText: 豪华型
data.enText: the de luxe/luxury version

data.chText: （从不同角度的）说法，描述
data.enText: a description of an event from the position of a particular person or group of people

data.chText: 她向我们描述了她认为那天发生的事情。
data.enText: She gave us her version of what had happened that day.

data.chText: 他们对事故发生情况的说法相互矛盾。
data.enText: Their versions of how the accident happened conflict.

data.chText: （电影、剧本、乐曲等的）版本，改编形式，改写本
data.enText: a film/movie, play, piece of music, etc. that is based on a particular piece of work but is in a different form, style or language

data.chText: 根据《战争与和平》改编的电影
data.enText: the film version of ‘War and Peace’

data.chText: 这部小说的英文译本预定明年出版发行。
data.enText: The English version of the novel is due for publication next year.

data.chText: 以上各词均指对所发生事情的记述、讲述。
data.enText: These are all words for a written or spoken account of events.
report

data.chText: 尤指刊登或广播的报道：
data.enText: a written or spoken account of an event, especially one that is published or broadcast

data.chText: 报纸上这些报道属实吗？
data.enText: Are these newspaper reports true?
description

data.chText: 指描写（文字）、形容、说明：
data.enText: a piece of writing or speech that says what sb/sth is like

data.chText: 该目录对每一种产品都作了详尽的说明。
data.enText: The catalogue gives a full description of each product.
story

data.chText: 常指对所发生事情的口头叙述、描述、（新闻）报道：
data.enText: an account, often spoken, of what happened to sb or of how sth happened; a report of events in a newspaper, magazine or news broadcast

data.chText: 许多年之后，事情的全貌才公之于众。
data.enText: It was many years before the full story was made public.

data.chText: 头版报道
data.enText: the front-page story
account

data.chText: 指对所发生事情的书面或口头描述、叙述、报告：
data.enText: a written or spoken description of sth that has happened

data.chText: 她向警方详尽地叙述了所发生的事情。
data.enText: She gave the police a full account of the incident.

data.chText: 用report还是account？
report总是指对最新事情的报道，尤指新闻报道。account可指对最近的或过去的事情的叙述。
data.enText: A report is always of recent events, especially news. An account may be of recent or past events.
report or account?
version

data.chText: 指特定的人或群体对某事的描述、说法：
data.enText: a description of an event from the point of view of a particular person or group of people

data.chText: 她从她的角度向我们描述了那天发生的事情。
data.enText: She gave us her version of what had happened that day.
a report/story about sth
a report on sth
a brief/short report/description/story/account
a long/lengthy report/description/account
a full report/description/story/account/version
a detailed report/description/account
a news report/story
to give a(n) report/description/account/version

simple_means.memory_skill: vers 转 + ion 表名词 → 从原文转换过来 → 译文

tr: manual turning of a fetus in the uterus (usually to aid delivery)
something a little different from others of the same type
example: an experimental version of the night fighter
a variant of the same word
an emery wheel is the modern variation of a grindstone
the boy is a younger edition of his father

tr: a mental representation of the meaning or significance of something
a written work (as a novel) that has been recast in a new form
example: the play is an adaptation of a short novel

tr: a written communication in a second language having the same meaning as the written communication in a first language
an interpretation of a matter from a particular viewpoint
example: his version of the fight was different from mine

value.def: A version of something is a particular form of it in which some details are different from earlier or later forms.

example.ex: Ludo is a version of an ancient Indian racing game...
example.tran: 鲁多是由一种古印度竞赛游戏演变而来。

example.ex: The second-hand version is a poor copy of the original.
example.tran: 盗版版本是对原版的低劣复制。

value.def: Someone's version of an event is their own description of it, especially when it is different to other people's.

example.ex: Yesterday afternoon the White House put out a new version of events...
example.tran: 昨天下午，白宫对事件给出了另一种说法。

example.ex: She and her friends wanted to go public with their version of the incident...
example.tran: 她和朋友们想把他们看到的事情经过公之于众。

example.ex: There have been widely differing versions in the newspapers about the prison siege.
example.tran: 关于围攻监狱一事，各家报纸众说纷纭，莫衷一是。
